elements.title:
Grounds from Peter Ramsey/Chelsea Wilson
1.       Suspected lack of testamentary capacity;
2.       Suspected undue influence;
3.       Will later than one being probated;
4.       Existence of a will and application is for grant of letters of administration;
5.       Applicant being improper person to receive estate grant
<br><br>
a CSB staff member could maybe do a search of them and record a summary of the reasons given (1 BC wide registry)

